!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

cream /kriːm/

(creaming,creamed,creams) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Cream is a thick yellowish-white liquid taken from milk. You can use it in cooking or put it on fruit or desserts. 奶油 

例： ...strawberries and cream. …草莓加奶油。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Cream is used in the names of soups that contain cream or milk. 奶油汤 [N 'of' n] 

例： ...cream of mushroom soup. …奶油蘑菇汤。 

3. N-VAR A cream is a substance that you rub into your skin, for example, to keep it soft or to heal or protect it. 膏; 霜 

例： Gently apply the cream to the affected areas. 轻轻地把药膏涂抹于患处。 

4. COLOR Something that is cream is yellowish-white in colour. 奶油色 

例： ...cream silk stockings. …乳白色的长筒丝袜。 

5.  →  see also ice cream

